-- U.K. Proposes Simplified Carbon Tax to Cut Costs for Business
-- B y   A l e x   M o r a l e s
-- 2012-03-27T11:34:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-27/u-k-plans-simpler-carbon-tax-to-cut-527-million-business-cost.html
The U.K. announced proposals to
simplify its emissions tax known as the Carbon Reduction
Commitment in a move the Department of Energy and Climate Change
said will save businesses and public bodies 330 million pounds
($527 million) by 2030, according to an e-mailed statement
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
